\ln|\sqrt{1+x^2}+x|+C
x = \sinh(t)
1+x^2 = 1+\sinh^2(t) = \cosh^2(t)
\mathrm{d}x = \sinh^\prime(t) \mathrm{d}t = \cosh(t) \mathrm{d}t
\cosh(t) >0 
t
\int \frac{\mathrm{d} x}{\sqrt{1+x^2}} = \operatorname{arcsinh}(x) + C
   \int \frac{\mathrm{d} x}{\sqrt{1+x^2}} = \int \frac{\cosh(t)}{\sqrt{\cosh^2(t)}} \mathrm{d} t = \int \mathrm{d} t = t + C 
